  "prompt": "What are all time best movies to watch?",
  "response": "There are countless movies that have stood the test of time and are often regarded as some of the best in cinematic history. Here\u2019s a compilation of all-time great films across various genres and eras:\n\n### Drama\n1. **The Godfather** (1972) - Directed by Francis Ford Coppola\n2. **Schindler's List** (1993) - Directed by Steven Spielberg\n3. **12 Angry Men** (1957) - Directed by Sidney Lumet\n4. **The Shawshank Redemption** (1994) - Directed by Frank Darabont\n\n### Romance\n5. **Casablanca** (1942) - Directed by Michael Curtiz\n6. **Gone with the Wind** (1939) - Directed by Victor Fleming\n7. **Titanic** (1997) - Directed by James Cameron\n\n### Comedy\n8. **Some Like It Hot** (1959) - Directed by Billy Wilder\n9. **Monty Python and the Holy Grail** (1975) - Directed by Terry Gilliam and Terry Jones\n10. **Groundhog Day** (1993) - Directed by Harold Ramis\n\n### Adventure/Fantasy\n11. **The Wizard of Oz** (1939) - Directed by Victor Fleming\n12. **Star Wars: Episode IV - A New Hope** (1977) - Directed by George Lucas\n13. **The Lord of the Rings: The Return of the King** (2003) - Directed by Peter Jackson\n\n### Science Fiction\n14. **2001: A Space Odyssey** (1968) - Directed by Stanley Kubrick\n15. **Blade Runner** (1982) - Directed by Ridley Scott\n16. **The Matrix** (1999) - Directed by Lana and Lilly Wachowski\n\n### Thriller/Horror\n17. **Psycho** (1960) - Directed by Alfred Hitchcock\n18. **The Silence of the Lambs** (1991) - Directed by Jonathan Demme\n19. **Get Out** (2017) - Directed by Jordan Peele\n\n### Animation\n20. **Spirited Away** (2001) - Directed by Hayao Miyazaki\n21. **The Lion King** (1994) - Directed by Roger Allers and Rob Minkoff\n22. **Toy Story** (1995) - Directed by John Lasseter\n\n### Foreign Films\n23. **Parasite** (2019) - Directed by Bong Joon-ho\n24. **Am\u00e9lie** (2001) - Directed by Jean-Pierre Jeunet\n25. **Cinema Paradiso** (1988) - Directed by Giuseppe Tornatore\n\nThis list only scratches the surface, and many more films could be included based on personal preferences and cultural significance. Whether you enjoy intense dramas, light-hearted comedies, or thought-provoking science fiction, there\u2019s something for everyone in cinema!",
